BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Brazil Raises Tax on Consumer Credit, Mantega

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-08T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/brazil-daybook-brazil-raises-tax-on-consumer-credit-mantega.html
Brazil  doubled a tax on  consumer
credit  to 3 percent a year from 1.5 percent in a bid to slow
inflation and contain consumer demand, Finance Minister  Guido
Mantega  said yesterday, after the markets closed.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega and JBS SA Chairman Joesley
Batista will speak at an event in Sao Paulo, starting at 9 a.m.
*Mines and Energy Minister Edison Lobao speaks about clean
energy and exploration of oil from Brazil’s pre-salt region in
an interview with the government´s NBR TV channel at 8 a.m.
*CPFL Energia SA, Brazil’s largest private-sector power
distributor, agreed to buy wind-energy producer Jantus SL for
950 million reais ($599 million).
*Brazil’s real strengthened beyond 1.60 per dollar for the first
time since August 2008.  ECONOMY: *FGV inflation IPC-S index at 8 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Cosan (CSAN3 BZ), Shell ethanol venture may refinance $2.5
billion debt
*Cyrela (CYRE3 BZ) has first-quarter sales of 998.6 million
reais
*Rodobens (RDNI3 BZ) has first-quarter sales 260 million reais  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.2 percent to 69,176.12
*The real rose 1.8 percent, the biggest gain since October, to
1.5863 per dollar  To contact the reporter on this story:
